OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F313A1783921779
OL,3,CA rivalry renewed: England's semi-
OL,4,Cfinal clash with Argentina
OL,6,F1986: Twenty years later, came the
OL,7,Finfamous "Hand of God goal", which
OL,8,Fhelped Argentina beat England 2-1. The
OL,9,Fhighly controversial goal, scored when
OL,10,FDiego Maradona punched the ball into
OL,11,Fthe net with his hand, was was allowed
OL,12,Fto stand by the Tunisian referee Ali
OL,13,FBin Nasser, much to the fury of the
OL,14,FEnglish team and its fans.
OL,16,FThe name "Hand of God goal" was
OL,17,FMaradona's tongue-in-cheek description
OL,18,Fof how it was scored. Argentina went
OL,19,Fon the win the tournament.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/15
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
