OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F313A1783921779
OL,3,CA rivalry renewed: England's semi-
OL,4,Cfinal clash with Argentina
OL,6,FBeckham had been fouled by Diego
OL,7,FSimeone, who rubbed his knuckles
OL,8,Fagainst the back of the England star's
OL,9,Fhead as he stood up. Beckham, who was
OL,10,Fstill lying face down on the pitch,
OL,11,Fswung his leg at Simeone, after which
OL,12,FSimeone fell over, and the referee
OL,13,Fsent England's No 7 off.
OL,15,FThe scores stayed level at 2`2 until
OL,16,Fthe end of extra time, but Argentina
OL,17,Fwon 4`3 after a nail-biting penalty
OL,18,Fshoot-out. Beckham faced a furious
OL,19,Fbacklash in the British press.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/15
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
